raw_data.title: Business Analyst I
raw_data.description: Provides support and / or management of the analysis needs of IT projects for clients through elicitation and documentation of business and system level requirements, impact assessments and ad-hoc analyses as needed to support project goals.  Work as a liaison among stakeholders to elicit, analyze, communicate, and validate business requirements and processes.  Develops process models, use cases, and scenarios in support of project activities.  Manages requirements and artifacts in requirements management tools.  Works with the customer to convert business requirements into functional, non-functional, and operational requirements.  Develops, reviews, maintains, and reviews feedback for process documentation.

raw_data.title: Program Director
raw_data.description: The Program Director is responsible for providing leadership to program management team and other assigned staff. Provides support to external and internal customers regarding programs and projects.  The Program Director ensures that the program meets or exceeds expectations by overseeing all program activities to include, but not limited to, schedule, scope, budget, risk and quality control.  Serves as a primary liaison between the client and the company, facilitating activities between the company, customers and partners, providing continual status reports and resolving issues in a timely manner.  Explores methods for improvement, and makes recommendations for improving and/or enhancing the program.  Actively engages in change management with stakeholders to ensure successful acceptance and readiness of delivered solution.

The Project Manage is responsible for developing and executing project tasks and activities as directed by the customer.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer I
raw_data.description: The Software Engineer develops and maintains software in accordance with project and customer requirements.  Implement highly scalable components and reliable web applications in a high traffic transactional data and data warehouse environment using the latest technologies following software engineering best practices.  Develops data persistence based on commercial and open source relational databases.  Provides thorough and automated unit test harnesses for developed solutions.  Provides software development estimates outlining business and technical risks.  Develops and deploys systems in an iterative, incremental process that fully incorporates testing.  Contributes to enterprise software development initiatives. Participates in formal requirement, design, and code reviews.  Regularly updates technical and business teams as to plans, progress, and issues. Analyzes, modifies and unit tests software in support of customer concerns.

raw_data.title: Systems Engineer II
raw_data.description: A System Engineer is responsible for the design, implementation and maintenance of technology systems, specifically working with hardware, network, application integration and deployments.  Typically, this is a technical leadership position for the Systems Engineer labor category.  The Senior System Engineer is responsible for leading technical engineering teams through the design, implementation and maintenance of technology systems, specifically working with hardware, network, application integration and deployments.  A Senior Systems Engineer can specialize in one or more of the following disciplines.  System <Hardware> Engineer, System <Network> Engineer or System <Integration> Engineer.  The Senior System <Hardware> Engineer focuses on leading and managing the design, implementation and maintenance of hardware computerized systems, such as web servers, application servers and database servers.  The Senior System <Network> Engineer focuses on leading and managing the design, implementation and maintenance of network systems, including firewalls, cabling and connection routing.  The Senior System <Integration> Engineer focuses on leading and managing the software application build, deployments and overall Configuration Management (CM) procedures including code compilation processes, software release processes.  Depending on the size of the specific project, an individual System Engineer may server multiple roles or a single specified role (hardware, network, integration).
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: An associate degree will equal 2 years of experience. A relevant bachelor’s degree will equal 4 years of experience. A relevant Master’s Degree will equal 6 years of experience. A Doctorate will equal 8 years of experience.

labor_categories.years_experience: An associate degree will equal 2 years of experience. A relevant bachelor’s degree will equal 4 years of experience. A relevant Master’s Degree will equal 6 years of experience. A Doctorate will equal 8 years of experience.
